---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Containing FU — Scrabble Word List & Strategy"
  description="Complete list of Scrabble words containing FU with scores, definitions, and strategic tips. Master FU words for better Scrabble plays."
  keywords="scrabble words containing fu, fu words scrabble, words with fu, scrabble fu word list, fu scrabble strategy"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Containing FU — Scrabble Word List & Strategy",
    "description": "Complete list of Scrabble words containing FU with scores, definitions, and strategic tips.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-containing-fu" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the highest-scoring FU words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Top FU words include FUZZY (29 pts), FUZZ (25 pts), FURZY (20 pts), FUNKY (15 pts), and CAREFUL (12 pts). FU paired with Z or Y produces exceptionally high scores." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many Scrabble words contain FU?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Over 500 valid Scrabble words contain FU. Common examples include FUN, FUR, FUEL, FULL, FUND, FURY, FUSE, FUTURE, REFUSE, USEFUL, CAREFUL, and FUZZY." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What strategy works best with FU tiles?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "FU excels when paired with Z — FUZZY (29 pts) and FUZZ (25 pts) are among the highest-scoring short words in Scrabble. FUNKY (15 pts) uses the K tile effectively. Short plays like FUN (6 pts) and FUR (6 pts) clear the F tile cheaply." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Containing FU — Scrabble Word List & Strategy</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">FU is a scoring powerhouse when Z is available. FUZZY (29 pts) and FUZZ (25 pts) are elite plays. FUNKY (15 pts) uses the K tile strongly. The pair appears in -FUL words (USEFUL, CAREFUL, PAINFUL) for reliable suffixed plays. FUN (6 pts) and FUR (6 pts) clear tiles when needed.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top FU Words by Score</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
